OL,4,CArchbishop of Canterbury issues
OL,5,C'personal apology' over charity abuse
OL,6, The Archbishop of Canterbury has issued
OL,7, a "full personal apology" to the
OL,8, survivors of abuse by former barrister
OL,9, John Smyth QC in the 1970s and 80s.
OL,11,FSmyth, who died aged 77 in 2018,
OL,12,Fviolently beat boys who attended
OL,13,FChristian summer camps.
OL,15,FJustin Welby said: "I am sorry this was
OL,16,Fdone in the name of Jesus Christ by a
OL,17,Fperverted version of spirituality and
OL,18,Fevangelicalism."
OL,20,FSurvivors who recently met Mr Welby
OL,21,Fwelcomed him "taking responsibility".
